sql:
SELECT category_id, COUNT(product_id) AS product_count
FROM product_category_map
GROUP BY category_id;

external_knowledge:
'Home and Kitchen' refers to a category of products; 

 A product is considered to have been "actively promoted" if its promotion is currently active (is_active = 1); 

 Promotion period refers to the time period between the promotion's start date and end date.

 A product is considered to have been "sold during its promotion period" if its order date falls within the promotion period.
